
== '''Pangasinan''' ==

----

'''Contents'''

'''English
Pronunciation'''

Pan-ga-si-nan
Pang-asin-an

'''Noun
Pangasinan (plual:  Pangasinans)'''

1.  A language belonging to the Austonesian language family spoken in the Philippines, primarily in the province of Pangasinan.
2.  The native speakers of the Pangasinan language.
3.  The name of a province of the Philippines in the island of Luzon.

'''Adjective
Pangasinan'''

1.  Pertaining to the people who speak the Pangasinan language.

